</font></td></tr>
</table></center>
<table width=70%>
<tr><td>Mana:</td>
<td>60</td></tr>
<tr><td>Skill:</td>
<td>Alteration</td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top>
Classes:</td>
<td>
<a href="/spells/cleric.shtml">
Cleric</a>
 (34)<BR>
</td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top>Items:</td>
<td>
<a href="/weapons/2h_blunt.shtml#water_sprinkler_of_the_forgiven">Water Sprinkler of the Forgiven</a><br>
</td></tr>
<tr><td>Buyable:</td><td>
Yes</td></tr>
<tr><td>Researchable:</td><td>
No</td></tr>
<tr><td>Drops from MOB:</td><td>
No</td></tr>
<tr><td>Cast Time:</td>
<td>4.00 seconds</td></tr>
<tr><td colspan=2><br></td></tr>
<tr><td colspan=2>Description:</td></tr>
<tr><td colspan=2>
Memory wipes the target.</td></tr>
<tr><td colspan=2>
<BR>1 tick = 6 seconds<BR>
When a range of effects are given, it usually means that the effect becomes more potent as the caster increases in levels.
