<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Boudar</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-09 23:54:12</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>What exactly does Atone do?  </font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Gylok Lifebringer</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-10 08:32:38</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>What atone does is wipe the aggro list of the mob.  This is particularly useful when trying to escape from a monster when used in conjunction with root.  In a party it can be useful also get get a mob off you when again you use root.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: </font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-27 15:17:49</font></td></tr><tr>
